daily_routine: Each morning at 4 AM, Aput checks ice conditions via satellite imagery
  on his tablet, comparing current ice thickness to GPS coordinates his grandfather
  carved into walrus ivory. He spends hours maintaining his qamutiik (traditional
  sled) and checking his seal hunting equipment, though he hasn't been able to use
  either in three weeks due to unsafe ice conditions
