environmental_stressor: Arctic sea ice forming 6 weeks later and breaking up 8 weeks
  earlier each year, eliminating the stable ice platform essential for traditional
  seal hunting
family_situation: Divorced father of two teenagers who moved to Iqaluit for high school.
  His ex-wife works for the territorial government and believes traditional hunting
  is "no longer viable." His son wants to learn traditional skills but there's no
  ice to teach on
